-- Polish WIG20 Heads for October Low as PKO Trades Without Dividend Rights
-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 2010-10-20T07:16:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/polish-wig20-heads-for-october-low-as-pko-trades-without-dividend-rights.html
Poland’s benchmark WIG20 Index fell
as much as 1.3 percent to 2,592.69, heading for the lowest close
this month as PKO Bank Polski SA, the country’s biggest bank,
started trading without the right to a dividend.  PKO retreated 4.5 percent to 43.95 zloty at 9:15 a.m. in
Warsaw. Excluding the 1.9-zloty dividend, the share price
slipped 0.4 percent today. The company has a 15 percent
weighting within the WIG20 Index.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Pawel Kozlowski at 
 pkozlowski@bloomberg.net  